"response_text": "The number of households adhering to the E-RO strategy begins the simulation at a level of 20. During the initial phase, the count experiences a minor upward fluctuation, reaching a local maximum of 21.1 around timestep 8. Following this early peak, the series enters a phase of sustained decline. This downward trajectory is statistically significant from approximately timestep 11 through timestep 65, driving the population count lower relative to the start. After timestep 65, the rate of decline moderates, and statistical tests indicate no significant trend between steps 66 and 98, suggesting the count has stabilized. By the conclusion of the 100-timestep run, the number of E-RO households settles at 14.7. This progression illustrates an initial period of volatility and reduction in the non-learning agent cohort, which eventually transitions into a stable long-term equilibrium."
}

